cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with vehicular safety communications, which involves wireless networking and communication protocols. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the outage probability and decoding strategies, which are concepts related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with modeling and analyzing the performance of a system (VSC) in the presence of interference. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper involves modeling the locations of interferer vehicles as a Poisson point process, which is a concept related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of VSC at intersections, which is a topic related to performance evaluation.
